Dear all, 
I am using Cantera through the Matlab toolbox. I have just 
expe=
rienced some problems when calling for critical properties of 
gas mixtures=
. 

All critical properties calls; critTemperature, critDensity and 
critPr=
essure gives this same type of error message. 

For example, this matlab co=
de=85

gas =3D GRI30;
air =3D set(gas,'T',298,'P',oneatm,'X','O2:0.21,N2:0.=
79');
Tc  =3D critTemperature(air);

=85gives the following error message:
=

??? Unexpected unknown exception from MEX file.

Error in =3D=3D> @ThermoP=
hase\private\thermo_get at 3
  i =3D ctmethods(20,n, job);

Error in =3D=3D=
> ThermoPhase.critTemperature at 4
  v =3D thermo_get(a.tp_id,19);

I would=
 very much appreciate if someone could give me some 
input/hints on how to =
deal with this.

Anders
